1
00:00:17,152 --> 00:00:19,208
<i>♫ Set off ♫</i>

2
00:00:19,968 --> 00:00:23,584
<i>♫ With the latte I just brewed ♫</i>

3
00:00:23,584 --> 00:00:28,907
<i>♫ And the long-lost sunshine in early summer ♫</i>

4
00:00:30,304 --> 00:00:33,731
<i>♫ What about them ♫</i>

5
00:00:33,731 --> 00:00:37,152
<i>♫ Are they waiting for an answer ♫</i>

6
00:00:37,152 --> 00:00:42,304
<i>♫ When the breeze brushes the cheek,
stirring a strand of hair ♫</i>

7
00:00:42,304 --> 00:00:48,032
<i>♫ Whisper to me ♫</i>

8
00:00:48,032 --> 00:00:51,424
<i>♫ Spring grows, summer extends ♫</i>

9
00:00:51,424 --> 00:00:54,304
<i>♫ Blooming freely ♫</i>

10
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,329
<i>♫ Is it all you ♫</i>

11
00:00:57,728 --> 00:01:01,865
<i>♫ It's all you ♫</i>

12
00:01:01,865 --> 00:01:05,184
<i>♫ Autumn harvest, winter storage ♫</i>

13
00:01:05,184 --> 00:01:08,106
<i>♫ Season changes ♫</i>

14
00:01:08,106 --> 00:01:10,198
<i>♫ With you ♫</i>

15
00:01:14,528 --> 00:01:16,867
<i>♫ With you ♫</i>

16
00:01:24,224 --> 00:01:28,640
[Episode 1 Grudges Shall Always be Avenged]

17
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:02,799
Hello.

18
00:02:02,799 --> 00:02:08,000
<i>Chi Cheng, I recently got a new snake.
Do you dare to come?</i>

19
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,519
Just wait for me.

20
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:37,200
Huang Long, it's your turn.

21
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,199
Mom, I'll do it.

22
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:48,319
It's fine, let me do it. Today,
my future daughter-in-law is coming.

23
00:02:48,319 --> 00:02:49,319
Thank you, mom.

24
00:02:49,319 --> 00:02:53,040
Look, I bought three jins of crayfish for Yue Yue.

25
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:57,680
Mom, this doesn't even weigh three jins at all.

26
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,919
What?

27
00:02:58,919 --> 00:03:04,399
Ms. Liu knew my future daughter-in-law is coming,
so she even gave me ten extra crayfish.

28
00:03:14,039 --> 00:03:17,360
Mom, she fooled you.
It definitely isn't three jins.

29
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:20,000
Half bag is just water, I'm going to find her.

30
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,639
Son, don't go.

31
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:24,199
It's difficult for Ms. Liu to run a business.

32
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:25,199
Don't cause her trouble.

33
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:28,120
- Mom.
- I've told you that suffering is a blessing.

34
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:29,919
The more sufferings, the more blessings.

35
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:32,840
Yes, Mom. We've been like this
for all these years.

36
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,439
But today isn't different.
Yue Yue is coming today.

37
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:40,120
Right, why isn't she here yet?

38
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,920
It's okay.

39
00:03:43,719 --> 00:03:47,280
She's always late when we date.
She's probably nearby now.

40
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,999
It's hard to find our place,
I'll go to pick her up.

41
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:58,880
<i>This place is smelly and dirty.</i>

42
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:10,120
Yue Yue.

43
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:13,320
Yue Yue, you're here.

44
00:04:14,319 --> 00:04:16,480
We can go eat now.
My mom has already prepared the meal.

45
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:20,759
My mom is really happy knowing that you're coming.

46
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:24,199
I'm not here for the meal.
I have something to tell you.

47
00:04:24,199 --> 00:04:26,480
Yue Yue, go ahead.

48
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:29,360
Wu Qi Qiong, let's break up.

49
00:04:31,279 --> 00:04:34,000
Why, Yue Yue? Why do you say that?

50
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,120
Didn't you promise to come to my house
for the meal? Why so sudden?

51
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:40,240
What? I used to be attracted by you
because you were handsome.

52
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:43,920
But look at you now,
being with you makes me feel ashamed.

53
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,720
Yue Yue, what do you like?
I can change myself for you.

54
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,519
I can change back, Yue Yue.

55
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:52,600
We've been together for so long.
And we're about to get married.

56
00:04:55,279 --> 00:04:58,079
Wang Zhen Long, what did you do?

57
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,680
Look at him, such a loser.

58
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,720
Why waste words to him?

59
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,600
Go for it!

60
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,680
Go for it, Mr. Guo!

61
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,720
Go for it!

62
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,520
Go for it!

63
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:30,160
Today, you're destined to lose.

64
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:44,920
Weren't they the best buddies?
Aren't they tired after many years of competing?

65
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:48,680
Do you think Mr. Chi's snake will win,
or Mr. Guo's?

66
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:51,600
Of course Mr. Chi's. He always wins.

67
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:55,879
I heard that Mr. Guo bought the black snake
from South America at great expense.

68
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:59,000
Today, Mr. Guo must make a comeback.

69
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Go for it!

70
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,040
Go for it, Mr. Guo!

71
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,199
- Get it!
- Get it!

72
00:06:02,199 --> 00:06:03,920
- Go for it!
- Get it!

73
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,720
Mr. Guo's snake has a chance.

74
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,400
- Get it!
- Get it!

75
00:06:11,839 --> 00:06:13,439
Mr. Guo is going to win.

76
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:16,239
Kill it! Go for it!

77
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:21,879
Bite it!

78
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,480
Bite it!

79
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,040
- Go for it!
- Bite it!

80
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,840
Bite it!

81
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,840
Go for it!

82
00:06:50,439 --> 00:06:52,319
Lost again.

83
00:06:52,319 --> 00:06:53,319
Good!

84
00:06:53,319 --> 00:06:55,840
Mr. Chi.

85
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,160
It's all right, guys.

86
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:11,160
Though I lost, I'm still happy.

87
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,240
Mr. Guo is magnanimous.

88
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,240
Mr. Guo is awesome.

89
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:15,079
Thank you, Mr. Guo.

90
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:17,079
Mr. Guo, I love you.

91
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:20,400
Mr. Chi is awesome.

92
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:25,559
Rest assured, I'm willing to accept defeat.

93
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:28,639
Spoils of war.

94
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:31,119
Spoils of war.

95
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,720
Forget it if you don't want to give me.

96
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,319
Li Wang.

97
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:42,119
Come on.

98
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:50,720
Long, this is my good buddy, Chi Cheng.

99
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,559
Go entertain him.

100
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:57,280
I've given you the person, have fun.

101
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:09,040
Chi Cheng!

102
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,840
Chi Cheng!

103
00:08:16,060 --> 00:08:18,713
[181s Glinic]

104
00:08:21,639 --> 00:08:24,120
Dr. Jiang, I know you like desserts,

105
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:26,720
so I made you this cake.

106
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,720
Thank you, Ms. Mei Li.

107
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,520
You're welcome.

108
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:38,320
Mr. Li, this isn't good for your cervical spine.
Use a mirror.

109
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:41,120
Right, my girl just bought me a lipstick.

110
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,440
Did Wu Qi Qiong wake up?

111
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:45,599
Yes. Is this for me?

112
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,000
You glutton.

113
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,640
You're fine now.

114
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,200
It hurts.

115
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:21,120
Don't move, I just changed your medication.

116
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,519
Where am I?

117
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:26,279
This is a clinic. Your friends brought you here.

118
00:09:26,279 --> 00:09:28,079
Friends?

119
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,639
Take it slow.

120
00:09:31,639 --> 00:09:33,120
A woman?

121
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,919
A man and a woman.

122
00:09:34,919 --> 00:09:37,240
The woman told me

123
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:41,520
to use the cheapest medicine available,
and make sure it's reimbursable.

124
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,360
She understands me best.

125
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:47,160
Let me tell you, she's my girlfriend.

126
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,240
- Girlfriend?
- Yes.

127
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:52,040
Then who is that man?

128
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,639
That man might be her friend.

129
00:09:56,639 --> 00:10:00,280
Or perhaps a nice guy.

130
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:02,879
A nice guy.

131
00:10:02,879 --> 00:10:05,760
Bro, it seems like you've been jilted.

132
00:10:09,279 --> 00:10:10,679
Alright, I admit it.

133
00:10:10,679 --> 00:10:13,639
Actually, it's not her fault.

134
00:10:13,639 --> 00:10:18,880
Because I've become ugly,
unfashionable, and fat now.

135
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:24,479
I think you can change.

136
00:10:27,039 --> 00:10:28,360
Really?

137
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,160
Trust me.

138
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,728
<i>First shave your beard</i>

139
00:10:34,784 --> 00:10:36,896
<i>and get a cool haircut.</i>

140
00:10:37,536 --> 00:10:39,080
The cooler, the better.

141
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,080
Okay.

142
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,120
Can you get me a haircut like him?

143
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,240
No problem.

144
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:44,760
<i>Dress in a clean style.</i>

145
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,497
[250 yuan]

146
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:54,120
<i>Losing weight is the hardest part,
but you must keep at it.</i>

147
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,639
<i>If you make a big change,</i>

148
00:10:56,639 --> 00:10:59,679
<i>your girlfriend will surely change her mind.</i>

149
00:11:11,279 --> 00:11:12,399
I'm here again.

150
00:11:12,399 --> 00:11:13,200
- Okay.
- Here.

151
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,639
Congratulations on collecting them all.

152
00:11:14,639 --> 00:11:16,439
Thank you.

153
00:11:37,159 --> 00:11:41,800
I made it!

154
00:12:00,879 --> 00:12:01,879
Hello.

155
00:12:01,879 --> 00:12:03,519
<i>Son, where are you?</i>

156
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:07,360
<i>Your dad is hospitalized, come back now.</i>

157
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:10,160
Alright, got it.

158
00:12:11,279 --> 00:12:12,480
I know.

159
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,600
It's okay.

160
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,400
Mr. Chi.

161
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,120
Take care of the snakes.

162
00:12:20,759 --> 00:12:23,559
What's the matter? Are you jealous?

163
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:25,359
Little Jealousy.

164
00:12:37,879 --> 00:12:39,679
Mom.

165
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:46,039
Why did you bring this thing back again?

166
00:12:46,039 --> 00:12:47,399
Aren't you at the hospital with dad?

167
00:12:47,399 --> 00:12:51,120
A caregiver is there,
so I came back to wait for you.

168
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,120
Let's go.

169
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,720
Where to?

170
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,559
To the hospital to see my dad.

171
00:12:57,799 --> 00:13:00,039
No rush, let's go tomorrow.

172
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:02,319
Anyway, your dad is asleep right now.

173
00:13:03,279 --> 00:13:05,319
I should have come back tomorrow.

174
00:13:06,399 --> 00:13:08,199
I'm going to sleep first, mom.

175
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:12,079
Can't you keep me accompany for longer?

176
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,279
Speak.

177
00:13:35,279 --> 00:13:36,879
<i>Mr. Chi, terrible.</i>

178
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:38,679
<i>The snake lair was taken.</i>

179
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:42,639
What did you say?

180
00:13:42,639 --> 00:13:45,000
<i>The snake lair was taken.</i>

181
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,200
Why?

182
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,519
<i>I don't know.</i>

183
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:50,919
I suspect Da Kun and I
might have been drugged last night.

184
00:13:50,919 --> 00:13:54,480
We slept very deeply, and when we woke up,
it's after nine in the morning.

185
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:58,679
All the snakes in the glass box are gone,
and the ones in your room were taken too.

186
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:01,200
Where is Long?

187
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:04,719
I don't know. He is gone.

188
00:14:11,679 --> 00:14:15,800
Stop talking, find Long.

189
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,880
Aren't you hospitalized?

190
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:23,920
<i>Lured me away?</i>

191
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,920
I knew it.

192
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:31,240
I've arranged everything.

193
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:34,800
You'll start working
at the Property Department next week.

194
00:14:36,159 --> 00:14:37,159
I use the back door.

195
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:38,959
How dare you!

196
00:14:43,879 --> 00:14:46,519
Look at you, how frivolous.

197
00:14:46,519 --> 00:14:50,360
You're already 28,
yet don't even get a decent job.

198
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:54,360
Guo Cheng Yu runs the company so well.

199
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:58,000
He is also frivolous,
but doesn't neglect business.

200
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:02,080
You can let him call you Dad. I'm fine with that.

201
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:04,080
I want him to be my son.

202
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:07,840
People called the complaint line to my office,

203
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,600
saying that my son is a weirdo
and with a chaotic private life.

204
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:13,319
I'm so embarrassed.

205
00:15:21,159 --> 00:15:26,559
If you want your snakes to live well,
then go to work.

206
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:37,920
Table A36. Table A36.

207
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:52,360
Yue Yue, you're here.

208
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,399
Look, I've lost weight.

209
00:15:54,399 --> 00:15:56,759
Let's go. I'll take you
to eat something delicious.

210
00:15:56,759 --> 00:16:00,240
Wu Qi Qiong, can you stop bothering me?

211
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:04,159
I am here to tell you
that we can't be together anymore.

212
00:16:04,159 --> 00:16:05,559
Don't send me messages anymore.

213
00:16:05,559 --> 00:16:07,720
Why, Yue Yue?

214
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:11,559
You used to hate me for being fat,
messy, and unpresentable.

215
00:16:11,559 --> 00:16:13,440
And I've changed. I've changed them all.

216
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:17,679
It's not about that at all.
I just look down on you being poor.

217
00:16:17,679 --> 00:16:20,000
My friends around me
all carry luxury bags and eat lavish meals.

218
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,639
But with you, I am only eating
ramen noodles or spicy hot pot.

219
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:25,240
- Have you ever treated me to a nice meal?
- We are here now.

220
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:27,919
- Table A37. Here?
- I'm here.

221
00:16:27,919 --> 00:16:29,559
This is a famous restaurant,
and I've waited in line for over an hour.

222
00:16:29,559 --> 00:16:30,600
It's ready for dining.

223
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:33,120
Here. I have coupons.

224
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:35,120
[Stamp Collection]

225
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:39,120
This coupon can only be used for weekday lunches.

226
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,920
Sorry.

227
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:48,480
Yue Yue.

228
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:49,639
Yue Yue.

229
00:16:49,639 --> 00:16:51,720
Look, it's over a hundred yuan short.

230
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,759
Let's switch to another place, shall we?

231
00:16:53,759 --> 00:16:54,879
Let's go.

232
00:16:54,879 --> 00:16:58,319
Look at you. Please go find someone else.

233
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,040
Wang Zhen Long.

234
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,519
I've told you, why waste words with him?

235
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:07,799
Who are you?

236
00:17:07,799 --> 00:17:09,759
What?

237
00:17:09,759 --> 00:17:12,680
Wu Qi Qiong, never-ending poverty.

238
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:16,040
With this name, you'll never rise in life.

239
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,960
Let's go.

240
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:39,879
Hello, sir.

241
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,760
Alright, I'll be right there.

242
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,440
Sir.

243
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:52,839
What takes you so long?

244
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:56,720
You usually ask me for projects and a raise.

245
00:17:56,720 --> 00:18:00,319
But at critical moments, you're not available.
Why are you staring at me?

246
00:18:00,319 --> 00:18:04,039
I asked you to fix this. Why staring at me?

247
00:18:04,039 --> 00:18:05,359
Fix it.

248
00:18:05,359 --> 00:18:07,919
Alright, I'll fix it now.

249
00:18:29,519 --> 00:18:30,559
What are you doing?

250
00:18:30,559 --> 00:18:33,400
Sir, this part is broken. We need a new one.

251
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,960
This one.

252
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,599
This part was perfectly fine. Did you break it?

253
00:18:37,599 --> 00:18:39,839
No, it was broken.

254
00:18:39,839 --> 00:18:42,279
Wu Qi Qiong.

255
00:18:42,279 --> 00:18:46,559
You are really dumb.

256
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:49,319
Just cover the cost of the parts first.

257
00:18:49,319 --> 00:18:52,160
Next month, you go
to Finance Department for reimbursement.

258
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:54,100
The money I advanced last month
hasn't been reimbursed.

259
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:56,480
My salary this month is less than 5,000.

260
00:18:56,480 --> 00:19:00,200
If you think the company
treats you bad, you can quit.

261
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,279
Don't occupy the position here.

262
00:19:02,279 --> 00:19:06,559
How dare you negotiate with me? Look at you.

263
00:19:06,559 --> 00:19:07,920
Let me tell you,

264
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:11,759
if you pay the money today,
this matter will be over.

265
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:14,319
<i>Yue Yue despises me of being poor
and ran off with another man.</i>

266
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:18,359
<i>Now my leader bullies me.
Everyone looks down on me.</i>

267
00:19:24,599 --> 00:19:27,480
I quit now!

268
00:19:31,816 --> 00:19:36,117
[181s Glinic]

269
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:47,160
Wait, Wu Qi Qiong.

270
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:50,879
It's only been a few days, why are you here again?

271
00:19:51,799 --> 00:19:53,599
I've changed my name.

272
00:19:54,279 --> 00:19:56,000
To what?

273
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,800
Wu Suo Wei.

274
00:20:09,799 --> 00:20:11,639
I want to make a comeback.

275
00:20:12,519 --> 00:20:13,880
What?

276
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,680
I want to make a comeback.

277
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:17,480
What comeback?

278
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:22,886
I want to make a comeback!

279
00:20:22,886 --> 00:20:25,088
[I want to make a comeback.]

280
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,000
Welcome.

281
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,759
Thank you for taking me in.

282
00:20:34,759 --> 00:20:38,440
It's fine. I want someone
to help me look after the clinic anyway.

283
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,760
I want to start my own business,

284
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:44,960
but I'm afraid my mom will worry if she knew it.

285
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,720
Have you decided what to do then?

286
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,640
I've decided to sell candied figures.

287
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,759
<i>To set up a stall at the night market
near Xiwang City.</i>

288
00:20:51,759 --> 00:20:53,279
<i>I've heard the regulations are strict there.</i>

289
00:20:53,279 --> 00:20:56,079
<i>No worries, I've already scouted the spot.</i>

290
00:20:56,079 --> 00:20:59,359
- Candied figures for sale!
- Fruits for sale!

291
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:02,000
We manage everything meticulously.

292
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,319
The management fee is paid on time.

293
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,000
They're coming, go now!

294
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,079
Wait for me.

295
00:21:10,079 --> 00:21:12,200
Sir, why are they running?

296
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:16,880
This street belongs to the Yuan Duan Group,
you need a stall permit to set up a stall here.

297
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:19,799
Without a permit, they'd run
when they see someone checking.

298
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:21,279
So, did you get a permit?

299
00:21:21,279 --> 00:21:25,119
I'm a small business
and often change places, it's not necessary.

300
00:21:25,119 --> 00:21:26,599
Aren't you afraid of getting caught?

301
00:21:26,599 --> 00:21:28,240
Let me tell you,

302
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:31,200
that person is named Hei,
and he's been looking out for us.

303
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:34,000
Average junior managers
don't dare to provoke him at all.

304
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,279
- That's great.
- Melons from Xinjiang.

305
00:21:36,279 --> 00:21:38,240
- Mr. Chi.
- What's all the shouting about?

306
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:40,640
That big-bearded guy is the scumbag.

307
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:43,519
He often bullies others.

308
00:21:43,519 --> 00:21:45,799
Let's see how Hei teaches him a lesson.

309
00:21:45,799 --> 00:21:48,240
Go die!

310
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:49,240
Great!

311
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,440
What are you doing?

312
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,079
What are you looking at?

313
00:21:52,079 --> 00:21:53,879
You…

314
00:22:06,279 --> 00:22:08,079
You deserve it.

315
00:22:19,039 --> 00:22:22,599
Sir, this guy in the suit is cool.

316
00:22:22,599 --> 00:22:24,720
Make way.

317
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:28,880
You deserve it. Get up!

318
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,880
Mr. Chi.

319
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:33,319
When dealing with these unruly stall vendors,
we have to be tough.

320
00:22:33,319 --> 00:22:35,119
Watch how I handle them.

321
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:44,520
Hey.

322
00:23:11,759 --> 00:23:13,640
Li Wang, you know him?

323
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:15,440
I don't know him.

324
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:22,119
Mr. Chi, chase him.

325
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,000
You!

326
00:23:25,839 --> 00:23:28,040
I'll catch you!

327
00:23:29,039 --> 00:23:32,800
Let's get to know this guy.

328
00:23:38,039 --> 00:23:39,480
What's the matter? You're nervous.

329
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,519
If there's someone coming for me,

330
00:23:41,519 --> 00:23:44,039
don't tell him I'm here.

331
00:23:44,039 --> 00:23:45,640
Alright, hide in there first.

332
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,759
- Okay.
- Don't make a sound.

333
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:48,559
Okay.

334
00:23:49,279 --> 00:23:51,079
Don't make a sound.

335
00:24:08,799 --> 00:24:10,039
What's up?

336
00:24:10,039 --> 00:24:11,119
Looking for someone.

337
00:24:11,119 --> 00:24:12,240
Who are you looking for?

338
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,440
Well…

339
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:16,799
Looking for you for diagnosis.

340
00:24:16,799 --> 00:24:19,760
Alright, take a seat.

341
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,680
Tell me, what's your problem?

342
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:26,359
Guess.

343
00:24:26,359 --> 00:24:29,240
If it's a gynecological issue,
go to the obstetrics and gynecology hospital.

344
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:32,399
Turn left and walk 30 meters,
then take metro line two.

345
00:24:34,599 --> 00:24:36,599
You're really pretty.

346
00:24:39,519 --> 00:24:43,200
If you're cross-eyed,
go to Tongren Hospital for consultation.

347
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,800
You like men, don't you?

348
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:55,599
If you have a psychiatric issue,
go to the psychiatric hospital.

349
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:06,480
[Jiang Xiao Shuai]
Jiang Xiao Shuai.

350
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,800
I remember it.

351
00:25:15,279 --> 00:25:16,279
Did they leave?

352
00:25:16,279 --> 00:25:18,079
Yes.

353
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:24,000
What a bad day.

354
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:27,366
I can't do this stall work anymore.
I need to find another job.

355
00:25:27,366 --> 00:25:30,734
[181s Glinic]

356
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:45,800
Dr. Shuai, why haven't I seen you
with a girlfriend?

357
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:54,040
But I've had a boyfriend.

358
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,440
Sorry to disturb you.

359
00:26:01,319 --> 00:26:03,559
You like men?

360
00:26:10,079 --> 00:26:12,879
What? Scared?

361
00:26:17,519 --> 00:26:22,040
No, nothing.

362
00:26:22,839 --> 00:26:25,639
I'm leaving.

363
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,559
When did you take it?

364
00:26:38,559 --> 00:26:40,519
When you were just talking.

365
00:26:40,519 --> 00:26:44,640
My second startup is about to begin. Wish me luck.

366
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:46,440
Where are you going?

367
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:10,839
<i>Chi, you are absent
in the class reunion again this year.</i>

368
00:27:12,039 --> 00:27:14,720
I am too busy to come.

369
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,480
<i>What? Stop it.</i>

370
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:18,720
<i>You, Guo Cheng Yu,</i>

371
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:23,480
<i>and Wang Shuo who loves raising snakes
were really close before.</i>

372
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:25,280
<i>Now…</i>

373
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,640
<i>Okay, everyone.</i>

374
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:47,440
<i>After the two successful cases,
we're now looking for the third one.</i>

375
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:53,440
Found it! Let me show you.

376
00:27:56,359 --> 00:27:57,440
<i>Isn't it good?</i>

377
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:59,200
<i>Alright, let's test him.</i>

378
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,200
We've already connected the pinhole camera.

379
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,759
I'll record the whole process.

380
00:28:02,759 --> 00:28:05,800
Once I turn off the phone, a miracle happens.

381
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:29,760
Are you alright?

382
00:28:31,319 --> 00:28:33,119
Thank you.

383
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,240
You faked a fall?

384
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,720
You pretended to help me, but I can't fake a fall?

385
00:28:45,599 --> 00:28:48,119
Bro, I'm not a thief.

386
00:28:48,119 --> 00:28:51,680
I'm just recording a video. Here's your phone.

387
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:55,200
Bro, look, now you believe me, right?

388
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,000
I'm really not a thief.

389
00:28:58,559 --> 00:29:01,799
What do you want?

390
00:29:01,799 --> 00:29:04,760
I'm really not a thief, really.

391
00:29:08,559 --> 00:29:09,559
You brought yourself here.

392
00:29:09,559 --> 00:29:13,200
Wait, have we met before?

393
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:18,040
Bro, I have evidence to prove
I'm not a thief, let me show you.

394
00:29:21,559 --> 00:29:24,119
Look, I run an anti-pickpocket account.

395
00:29:24,119 --> 00:29:26,480
You're just a random passerby I picked.

396
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:28,920
This is to educate people
about some common thief tactics,

397
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:29,920
to avoid being stolen.

398
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:32,279
Trust me, bro. The livestream viewers
can vouch for me.

399
00:29:32,279 --> 00:29:34,920
Look.

400
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:37,919
Look, right?

401
00:29:38,559 --> 00:29:40,359
Right?

402
00:29:48,559 --> 00:29:50,960
What's your name?

403
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:51,960
Wu Suo Wei.

404
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:54,279
What? That arrogant?

405
00:29:54,279 --> 00:29:56,039
No.

406
00:29:56,039 --> 00:29:58,160
It's my real name.

407
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:01,240
I have evidence. Wait for me.

408
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:03,040
ID card.

409
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:04,880
Look.

410
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:07,584
[Wu Suo Wei]

411
00:30:08,319 --> 00:30:09,799
You are indeed named Wu Suo Wei.

412
00:30:09,799 --> 00:30:10,960
Right. It's all a misunderstanding.

413
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,639
- Quite unique.
- Not at all.

414
00:30:16,799 --> 00:30:18,599
Oh my.

415
00:30:19,599 --> 00:30:22,319
Why did you throw sugar at me that day?

416
00:30:23,279 --> 00:30:26,480
Bro, I didn't mean to.

417
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,880
I wanted to splash the one next to…

418
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:30,240
I didn't intend to splash you.

419
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:32,759
Bro, I was wrong.

420
00:30:32,759 --> 00:30:34,559
Sorry.

421
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,800
Bro.

422
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:45,680
Bro, don't go.

423
00:30:48,839 --> 00:30:49,839
Don't.

424
00:30:49,839 --> 00:30:51,680
Two options for you.

425
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,839
Either get beaten up by me,

426
00:30:55,559 --> 00:30:59,200
or have your device confiscated.

427
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,480
I choose to be beaten.

428
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,280
It's already settled.

429
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:06,519
Bro, give it back to me.

430
00:31:06,519 --> 00:31:08,400
I spent a lot of money on it, bro.
Give it back to me, please.

431
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,200
Bro!

432
00:31:17,279 --> 00:31:19,079
Mr. Chi.

433
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:31,559
Mr. Chi, I brought you the person.
He tried to escape abroad.

434
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:39,200
Mr. Chi, listen to me.

435
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:44,720
Your dad brought dozens of people to me,
and I was scared to death.

436
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:48,759
It was your dad who questioned me,
otherwise I wouldn't have told him anything.

437
00:31:48,759 --> 00:31:50,680
Don't lie.

438
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:54,480
The call to the chairman's office
was made by Guo Cheng Yu's men, right?

439
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:58,919
When the chairman drove to you,
you were long gone.

440
00:32:08,319 --> 00:32:10,119
Come here.

441
00:32:11,039 --> 00:32:14,440
Mr. Chi.

442
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,359
What do you guys think of him?

443
00:32:19,359 --> 00:32:22,680
Not bad, we all quite like him.

444
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,839
Everyone really likes you.

445
00:32:24,839 --> 00:32:26,599
Wait, wait.

446
00:32:26,599 --> 00:32:31,000
I'll leave him to you guys. I'm leaving.

447
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,759
Mr. Chi, Mr. Chi.

448
00:32:33,759 --> 00:32:35,440
- Good boy.
- Mr. Chi.

449
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:36,440
Get lost.

450
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:38,920
Mr. Chi, I'm sorry.

451
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:42,680
Mr. Chi, I was wrong.

452
00:32:43,799 --> 00:32:45,440
Let go of me.

453
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:47,440
- Watch out.
- Mr. Chi.

454
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,680
Don't let him die.

455
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:51,039
I was wrong, let me go.

456
00:32:51,039 --> 00:32:54,319
Let go. Mr. Chi.

457
00:32:56,134 --> 00:33:03,391
[Splendid Minghao]

458
00:33:05,039 --> 00:33:08,400
Whose car is blocking my way?

459
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:12,519
Darn!

460
00:33:12,519 --> 00:33:13,599
How did he park?

461
00:33:13,599 --> 00:33:15,399
Mr. Chi.

462
00:33:21,319 --> 00:33:23,200
Is it your car?

463
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:26,599
Drive away or it will be smashed.

464
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:34,559
What are you waiting for? Get lost.

465
00:33:58,279 --> 00:34:00,559
<i>This is the kind of man who deserves me.</i>

466
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:19,440
Don't touch me. Focus on driving.

467
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:21,240
What's wrong with you?

468
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,800
Nothing.

469
00:34:29,639 --> 00:34:31,519
Darn, he blinded me.

470
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:34,199
Slow down.

471
00:34:34,199 --> 00:34:36,479
Give way, give way.

472
00:34:49,079 --> 00:34:53,119
Wang Zhen Long, wake up.

473
00:34:53,119 --> 00:34:57,280
Wang Zhen Long, speak up.

474
00:36:01,199 --> 00:36:03,639
Why did you call me back?

475
00:36:03,639 --> 00:36:06,489
You're always like someone owes you money.

476
00:36:06,489 --> 00:36:07,920
I'll give you one year,

477
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:11,480
if you can't find a girlfriend,
I'll decide whom you'll marry.

478
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:14,360
Okay, as long as she's not afraid of snakes.

479
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:17,079
Do you really have to carry that with you?

480
00:36:17,079 --> 00:36:18,840
Our son doesn't have a girlfriend.

481
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:21,000
No matter what you say, he won't listen.

482
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:24,239
Once he has a girlfriend,
he'll understand what's important.

483
00:36:24,239 --> 00:36:26,039
Right, son?

484
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:30,960
Tell me,

485
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:32,340
Old Wang's son is half-paralyzed.

486
00:36:32,340 --> 00:36:35,079
Do you have anything to do with it?

487
00:36:35,079 --> 00:36:38,679
Who? I don't know him.

488
00:36:38,679 --> 00:36:39,920
It's best that way.

489
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:44,399
Let's go, Little Jealousy. Go home.

490
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:51,919
Leaving again. I don't even know
whom he takes after.

491
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:55,560
What do you think?

492
00:37:14,119 --> 00:37:16,519
<i>You finally appeared.</i>

493
00:37:29,079 --> 00:37:31,879
Shuai, you are still here?

494
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:45,359
I forgot you like men.

495
00:37:58,400 --> 00:38:02,039
Are you avoiding suspicion
or deliberately seducing me?

496
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:05,160
Sorry.

497
00:38:10,639 --> 00:38:14,039
What happened? It's like someone owes you money.

498
00:38:14,039 --> 00:38:15,559
Don't mention it.

499
00:38:15,559 --> 00:38:18,960
Can't do this live stream job.
My device was taken.

500
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:21,039
Then don't.

501
00:38:21,039 --> 00:38:24,680
Are there any other jobs I can do?

502
00:38:26,119 --> 00:38:28,519
I have a relative with a truck.

503
00:38:28,519 --> 00:38:32,599
He usually delivers some goods.
Why don't you join him?

504
00:38:32,599 --> 00:38:35,600
Payment by the task, and the time is flexible.

505
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,280
This works.

506
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:42,760
Sorry.

507
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:11,640
Recovered?

508
00:39:14,159 --> 00:39:17,120
Seeing you, I recovered.

509
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:20,720
Cheesy.

510
00:39:30,559 --> 00:39:32,840
Aren't you cold?

511
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:36,560
Of course, I'm feeling cold.

512
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,800
There's a python in my car.

513
00:39:41,039 --> 00:39:44,680
I like snakes. I'll go check.

514
00:40:07,679 --> 00:40:11,760
This snake is really cute.

515
00:40:20,599 --> 00:40:25,000
<i>Okay, I'll use you to comfort my dad</i>

516
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,999
<i>and take back my snakes.</i>

517
00:40:43,119 --> 00:40:47,079
We've searched everywhere we could,
and someone is watching the chairman's car.

518
00:40:47,079 --> 00:40:49,360
But his routine is regular every day.

519
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:53,600
Except for the company and home,
he hasn't gone anywhere else.

520
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,920
Is it possible that they're in the company?

521
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:10,450
No way.

522
00:41:10,450 --> 00:41:12,360
With this amount of snakes,

523
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:15,599
he has to prepare a large space
and dedicated people.

524
00:41:15,599 --> 00:41:19,400
If they're in the company, we must hear some news.

525
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:21,312
Did you forget?

